# Windows tools must keep CRLF in the repo so cmd.exe doesn't silently
# exit when users download these files raw from GitHub. `binary` is the
# only attribute that fully disables Git's line-ending normalization —
# `text eol=crlf` still stores LF in the repo, only restoring CRLF at
# checkout time, which doesn't help raw HTTPS downloads.
*.bat binary
*.cmd binary
*.ps1 binary
